jinghong, guangzhou, haikou and macau. europe: most of the major european airlines, including air france [24], british airways [25], and finnair [26] have direct flights from their hubs to hong kong, beijing and shanghai; several fly to guangzhou as well. a few have links to other chinese cities. for example klm [27]flies direct from amsterdam to chengdu, hangzhou and xiamen and lufthansa [28] flies a frankfurt to nanjing route. taiwan: regular direct flights between taiwan and mainland china resumed in 2008, after a 59 year ban. there are now daily direct flights between taipei and major cities in china. flights 